def merge_sorted_lists(list1_e, list2_e):
    result_e = []
    i, j = 0, 0

    while i < len(list1_e) and j < len(list2_e):
        if list1_e[i] < list2_e[j]:
            result_e.append(list1_e[i])
            i += 1
        else:
            result_e.append(list2_e[j])
            j += 1

    result_e.extend(list1_e[i:])
    result_e.extend(list2_e[j:])

    return result_e
